WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:12.178 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
Hello, again!

00:00:12.262 --> 00:00:14.305 position:50% align:center
It's your favorite bookworm
and inspiring intellectual!

00:00:14.389 --> 00:00:16.349 position:50% align:center
Wait. Aspiring? Insp...

00:00:16.433 --> 00:00:18.601 position:50% align:center
What'cha reading, Yashiro?

00:00:18.685 --> 00:00:20.937 position:50% align:center
[NENE] While I was in my new
favorite place, the library,

00:00:21.021 --> 00:00:22.605 position:50% align:center
I decided to read every
book that might have

00:00:22.689 --> 00:00:24.649 position:50% align:center
secret information on Hanako.

00:00:24.733 --> 00:00:26.943 position:50% align:center
That's how I learned about
the fifth of the Seven Wonders,

00:00:27.027 --> 00:00:29.029 position:50% align:center
the Four o'clock Library.

00:00:29.112 --> 00:00:31.239 position:50% align:center
If there's a book with
Hanako's school history in it,

00:00:31.322 --> 00:00:32.657 position:50% align:center
I want to find it!

00:00:32.741 --> 00:00:34.367 position:50% align:center
I just don't want
to go there alone.

00:00:34.451 --> 00:00:36.494 position:50% align:center
Um, hi?
I'm still here. I'll go!

00:00:42.208 --> 00:00:45.128 position:50% align:center
[bell rings]

00:00:48.256 --> 00:00:49.382 position:50% align:center
[KOU]
Hmm...

00:00:50.300 --> 00:00:52.677 position:50% align:center
You're bored, huh? I'm sorry.

00:00:52.761 --> 00:00:55.221 position:50% align:center
Me? Never!
Besides, you're my bro now.

00:00:55.305 --> 00:00:56.848 position:50% align:center
I'd do anything for you!

00:00:56.931 --> 00:00:58.725 position:50% align:center
And I may or may not
be a little curious to read

00:00:58.808 --> 00:01:00.518 position:50% align:center
his book myself.

00:01:00.602 --> 00:01:02.604 position:50% align:center
I had a
feeling that might be it.

00:01:02.687 --> 00:01:03.897 position:50% align:center
You're trying to find out
his weaknesses

00:01:03.980 --> 00:01:06.191 position:50% align:center
so you can exorcise him,
aren't you?

00:01:06.274 --> 00:01:07.275 position:50% align:center
Well...

00:01:08.485 --> 00:01:10.195 position:50% align:center
[TERU]
Don't even.

00:01:10.278 --> 00:01:12.947 position:50% align:center
There is no such thing
as a good apparition, Kou.

00:01:14.032 --> 00:01:15.575 position:50% align:center
I've been doing some thinking.

00:01:15.658 --> 00:01:18.453 position:50% align:center
And I honestly can't say I know
that much about the guy,

00:01:18.536 --> 00:01:21.122 position:50% align:center
or that I have a real reason
to exorcise him.

00:01:21.206 --> 00:01:23.667 position:50% align:center
Well, besides the fact
that he's a toilet germ.

00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:25.752 position:50% align:center
Can ghosts even get germs?

00:01:25.835 --> 00:01:28.004 position:50% align:center
I've only seen him
fight the bad guys.

00:01:28.088 --> 00:01:30.465 position:50% align:center
There doesn't seem to be
a reason to get rid of him.

00:01:30.548 --> 00:01:31.966 position:50% align:center
We're on the same page.

00:01:32.050 --> 00:01:34.594 position:50% align:center
I know we'll find
his book together!

00:01:34.678 --> 00:01:35.679 position:50% align:center
[KOU grunts]

00:01:38.848 --> 00:01:40.266 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
Um, are you okay?

00:01:46.106 --> 00:01:47.232 position:50% align:center
Look at that.

00:01:50.026 --> 00:01:51.027 position:50% align:center
[NENE yelps]

00:01:52.237 --> 00:01:53.238 position:50% align:center
[KOU]
Nene!

00:01:54.531 --> 00:01:55.657 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
Is this it?

00:01:55.740 --> 00:01:57.701 position:50% align:center
Is this the
Four o'Clock library?

00:02:05.875 --> 00:02:07.252 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
Omigosh.

00:02:07.335 --> 00:02:08.920 position:50% align:center
[KOU]
Looks like another Boundary.

00:02:09.004 --> 00:02:11.631 position:50% align:center
We're on the border between
this life and the next.

00:02:11.715 --> 00:02:13.341 position:50% align:center
Be extremely careful.

00:02:13.425 --> 00:02:14.759 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
It's kinda hard to see.

00:02:16.678 --> 00:02:17.595 position:50% align:center
[MOKKE A]
Need it?

00:02:17.679 --> 00:02:18.972 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
Yes, thank you!

00:02:21.933 --> 00:02:24.019 position:50% align:center
White books are records
for the living,

00:02:24.102 --> 00:02:26.521 position:50% align:center
and black ones are
records for the dead.

00:02:26.604 --> 00:02:27.731 position:50% align:center
That's what Aoi said.

00:02:27.814 --> 00:02:30.150 position:50% align:center
Cool, so we're looking
for a black book, then.

00:02:32.777 --> 00:02:35.238 position:50% align:center
Kou, look.
Another butterfly.

00:02:35.321 --> 00:02:37.449 position:50% align:center
Maybe it wants us to follow it?

00:02:37.532 --> 00:02:38.992 position:50% align:center
[KOU]
You can't just follow a bug!

00:02:39.075 --> 00:02:40.243 position:50% align:center
Come back!

00:02:45.457 --> 00:02:46.958 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
No way.

00:02:47.042 --> 00:02:48.251 position:50% align:center
Is this my book?

00:02:50.211 --> 00:02:52.088 position:50% align:center
[KOU gasps]

00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:53.798 position:50% align:center
[NENE] That means everything
I've done in school

00:02:53.882 --> 00:02:55.133 position:50% align:center
should be in here.

00:02:58.053 --> 00:03:00.805 position:50% align:center
Hanako took off his hat
for the first time today!

00:03:00.889 --> 00:03:03.224 position:50% align:center
It was like seeing
a whole new side of him.

00:03:03.308 --> 00:03:05.477 position:50% align:center
My raw feelings about this
can best be described

00:03:05.560 --> 00:03:07.687 position:50% align:center
in a poem.

00:03:07.771 --> 00:03:09.773 position:50% align:center
A glimpse of your bare eyes.

00:03:09.856 --> 00:03:11.941 position:50% align:center
I've wondered about
your disguise.

00:03:12.025 --> 00:03:12.942 position:50% align:center
Why?

00:03:13.026 --> 00:03:14.944 position:50% align:center
Why-fore since you
are not my type.

00:03:15.028 --> 00:03:17.072 position:50% align:center
Yet my heart believes the hype.

00:03:17.155 --> 00:03:21.659 position:50% align:center
I am oh so curious
about your love. Serious.

00:03:21.743 --> 00:03:22.744 position:50% align:center
[NENE yelps]

00:03:22.827 --> 00:03:24.621 position:50% align:center
What's goin' on in there?

00:03:24.704 --> 00:03:26.790 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
Oh, this isn't Hanako's book.

00:03:26.873 --> 00:03:29.334 position:50% align:center
But I've read a bit
and it looks like the rumors

00:03:29.417 --> 00:03:30.710 position:50% align:center
about the past
are true, at least.

00:03:30.794 --> 00:03:32.796 position:50% align:center
I wonder if I should
look at the future.

00:03:32.879 --> 00:03:33.922 position:50% align:center
[KOU]
Duh!

00:03:36.716 --> 00:03:38.134 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
A red page?

00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:41.096 position:50% align:center
This must be where records
on the future start.

00:03:41.179 --> 00:03:43.431 position:50% align:center
I don't know if I want
to find out, though.

00:03:44.516 --> 00:03:45.975 position:50% align:center
Seems scary.

00:03:46.059 --> 00:03:47.018 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:03:47.102 --> 00:03:49.354 position:50% align:center
What the crap? My first date?

00:03:49.437 --> 00:03:51.189 position:50% align:center
With who? Do we fall in love?

00:03:55.026 --> 00:03:56.736 position:50% align:center
Anyway, back to Hanako's life.

00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:01.324 position:50% align:center
Is this it?

00:04:07.122 --> 00:04:08.081 position:50% align:center
[NENE gasps]

00:04:08.164 --> 00:04:10.041 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
It's red! But how?

00:04:10.125 --> 00:04:11.710 position:50% align:center
It was white a second ago!

00:04:12.877 --> 00:04:14.546 position:50% align:center
I was about to find out
more on Hanako,

00:04:14.629 --> 00:04:16.172 position:50% align:center
and now I can barely read it!

00:04:19.676 --> 00:04:21.845 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
No wait, I can still kinda see.

00:04:27.892 --> 00:04:29.561 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
The name written here.

00:04:29.644 --> 00:04:31.563 position:50% align:center
Is this Hanako's real name?

00:04:36.943 --> 00:04:37.986 position:50% align:center
[KOU]
Watch out!

00:04:40.280 --> 00:04:42.282 position:50% align:center
[NENE gasps]
What was that thing?!

00:04:44.117 --> 00:04:46.244 position:50% align:center
No. Is that me?

00:04:48.413 --> 00:04:50.081 position:50% align:center
Bring it on, whatever you are!

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:53.376 position:50% align:center
Take that!

00:05:02.385 --> 00:05:06.973 position:50% align:center
I forgot he shut down my staff!
Hanako, you Flush Bucket!

00:05:07.057 --> 00:05:08.266 position:50% align:center
You rang?

00:05:22.572 --> 00:05:24.532 position:50% align:center
Hi! Nice to see you!

00:05:24.616 --> 00:05:25.825 position:50% align:center
You saved us.

00:05:25.909 --> 00:05:27.243 position:50% align:center
Thanks, Hanako.

00:05:31.581 --> 00:05:33.083 position:50% align:center
What's happening?

00:05:33.166 --> 00:05:35.210 position:50% align:center
Nothin', Honey Bear!

00:05:35.293 --> 00:05:37.212 position:50% align:center
[KOU]
Quit being awkward!

00:05:37.295 --> 00:05:38.421 position:50% align:center
[TSUCHIGOMORI]
Hey!

00:05:38.505 --> 00:05:40.090 position:50% align:center
What do you think
you're doing here?

00:05:40.173 --> 00:05:42.008 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
Oh, sorry sir! I don't know!

00:05:43.843 --> 00:05:44.886 position:50% align:center
Oh, great.

00:05:44.969 --> 00:05:45.970 position:50% align:center
You need to watch
where you're going.

00:05:46.054 --> 00:05:48.223 position:50% align:center
Look what you've done
to my books.

00:05:48.306 --> 00:05:49.599 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
Look behind you!

00:06:00.068 --> 00:06:01.111 position:50% align:center
[TSUCHIGOMORI]
This. 

00:06:01.194 --> 00:06:03.780 position:50% align:center
This is why I
hate kids so much.

00:06:03.863 --> 00:06:06.449 position:50% align:center
You're sticky, and you don't
know when to shut up.

00:06:08.159 --> 00:06:09.452 position:50% align:center
Hey!

00:06:09.536 --> 00:06:11.621 position:50% align:center
Well, now. I noticed that
the book has turned red.

00:06:11.705 --> 00:06:13.039 position:50% align:center
Let me guess,
you couldn't help yourself

00:06:13.123 --> 00:06:14.708 position:50% align:center
and read the future, right?

00:06:14.791 --> 00:06:16.251 position:50% align:center
Bad idea. Bad.

00:06:16.334 --> 00:06:17.877 position:50% align:center
[KOU]
Put me down please!

00:06:17.961 --> 00:06:19.504 position:50% align:center
I get really bad headaches!

00:06:25.385 --> 00:06:27.846 position:50% align:center
Now then, what shall
I do with you?

00:06:32.267 --> 00:06:33.977 position:50% align:center
It's not polite to tease them.

00:06:36.021 --> 00:06:38.481 position:50% align:center
Very well, then. I guess
you're right, Number Seven.

00:06:38.565 --> 00:06:39.941 position:50% align:center
I guess you're right.

00:06:40.025 --> 00:06:42.485 position:50% align:center
I suppose it's rude of me
to treat the boss's guests

00:06:42.569 --> 00:06:43.987 position:50% align:center
this way.

00:06:44.070 --> 00:06:46.031 position:50% align:center
[KOU]
Uh, Hanako? Who's this?

00:06:46.114 --> 00:06:48.241 position:50% align:center
Whoops.
I forgot to introduce you.

00:06:48.324 --> 00:06:51.286 position:50% align:center
This is Wonder Number Five.
Mr. Tsuchigomori.

00:06:51.369 --> 00:06:53.913 position:50% align:center
AKA The Four O' Clock Library.

00:06:53.997 --> 00:06:56.833 position:50% align:center
Wait, he's a teacher?
And the Fifth Wonder?

00:06:56.916 --> 00:06:58.293 position:50% align:center
Whoa, they've got
someone on staff here

00:06:58.376 --> 00:06:59.669 position:50% align:center
that's not even human?

00:07:01.880 --> 00:07:04.591 position:50% align:center
It's not as bizarre
as you may think it is.

00:07:04.674 --> 00:07:06.926 position:50% align:center
When you consider that we
apparitions cannot exist

00:07:07.010 --> 00:07:08.928 position:50% align:center
if our stories
aren't being told,

00:07:09.012 --> 00:07:11.056 position:50% align:center
you can see why we'd
want to take an active role

00:07:11.139 --> 00:07:13.141 position:50% align:center
in keeping the rumors alive.

00:07:13.224 --> 00:07:15.226 position:50% align:center
You may even have friends
that aren't exactly human

00:07:15.310 --> 00:07:17.979 position:50% align:center
anymore and not even
notice a difference.

00:07:18.063 --> 00:07:21.232 position:50% align:center
Really? Isn't that dangerous?

00:07:21.316 --> 00:07:22.942 position:50% align:center
More like uncomfortable.

00:07:23.026 --> 00:07:26.279 position:50% align:center
But it's never actually
unsafe with us around.

00:07:26.363 --> 00:07:28.490 position:50% align:center
Yako? What are you doing here?

00:07:28.573 --> 00:07:31.409 position:50% align:center
[YAKO] Ask Number Seven.
He summoned me.

00:07:31.493 --> 00:07:33.787 position:50% align:center
Yes, it's true,
apparitions scare humans,

00:07:33.870 --> 00:07:36.206 position:50% align:center
but sometimes it's the only
way to get your attention,

00:07:36.289 --> 00:07:39.376 position:50% align:center
so the seven of us make sure
the school remains peaceful.

00:07:39.459 --> 00:07:40.877 position:50% align:center
I lead the way.

00:07:40.960 --> 00:07:42.921 position:50% align:center
But there're only
three of you.

00:07:43.004 --> 00:07:45.382 position:50% align:center
Yako attacked students
until recently.

00:07:45.465 --> 00:07:46.883 position:50% align:center
She doesn't count.

00:07:46.966 --> 00:07:49.135 position:50% align:center
Gee, sounds like you
made a good impression.

00:07:49.219 --> 00:07:50.679 position:50% align:center
[YAKO] You should really
mind your own business,

00:07:50.762 --> 00:07:52.097 position:50% align:center
Mr. Spider Legs.

00:07:52.180 --> 00:07:53.640 position:50% align:center
[BOTH arguing]

00:07:53.723 --> 00:07:55.183 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
None of you work together.

00:07:55.266 --> 00:07:57.185 position:50% align:center
[KOU]
That whole speech was a lie!

00:07:57.268 --> 00:08:00.063 position:50% align:center
Stop! You're embarrassing me!

00:08:00.146 --> 00:08:01.481 position:50% align:center
Now, play nicely.

00:08:01.564 --> 00:08:02.691 position:50% align:center
[YAKO, TSUCHIGOMORI]
Yes, sir.

00:08:02.774 --> 00:08:04.776 position:50% align:center
[NENE] Okay, I guess
he really is the leader.

00:08:05.652 --> 00:08:07.904 position:50% align:center
As I was saying,
the seven of us work as a team

00:08:07.987 --> 00:08:10.365 position:50% align:center
to maintain the peace
at this school.

00:08:10.448 --> 00:08:12.784 position:50% align:center
However, it appears
that one of us

00:08:12.867 --> 00:08:15.620 position:50% align:center
has metamorphosed
into a traitor.

00:08:15.704 --> 00:08:18.289 position:50% align:center
They've found a way to forge
a bond with a human,

00:08:18.373 --> 00:08:20.667 position:50% align:center
and that human is spreading
rumors about apparitions

00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:23.003 position:50% align:center
that have been altered
to suit their needs.

00:08:23.086 --> 00:08:25.672 position:50% align:center
Number Two is one
of their victims.

00:08:25.755 --> 00:08:27.966 position:50% align:center
If it were only involving
Numberless apparitions,

00:08:28.049 --> 00:08:29.467 position:50% align:center
we wouldn't be concerned,

00:08:29.551 --> 00:08:32.929 position:50% align:center
but they are manipulating
truths about the Wonders.

00:08:33.013 --> 00:08:35.306 position:50% align:center
[YAKO] Which can only mean
that this criminal is a human

00:08:35.390 --> 00:08:36.975 position:50% align:center
with ties to a Wonder.

00:08:37.058 --> 00:08:40.353 position:50% align:center
Are you saying there
are other humans like me?

00:08:40.437 --> 00:08:43.440 position:50% align:center
[HANAKO] It would be extremely
difficult to find them.

00:08:43.523 --> 00:08:46.151 position:50% align:center
But I've come up
with a solution.

00:08:46.234 --> 00:08:49.154 position:50% align:center
We'll temporarily cancel
all Seven Wonders!

00:08:50.155 --> 00:08:51.031 position:50% align:center
What?

00:08:51.114 --> 00:08:52.282 position:50% align:center
Cancel?

00:08:52.365 --> 00:08:54.075 position:50% align:center
[HANAKO] We'll destroy
each Wonder's Yorishiro,

00:08:54.159 --> 00:08:56.536 position:50% align:center
and it will lose its power.

00:08:56.619 --> 00:08:58.788 position:50% align:center
Then we won't have to worry
about finding the traitor,

00:08:58.872 --> 00:09:01.458 position:50% align:center
or everything becoming
a mad mess.

00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:04.419 position:50% align:center
Sounds like we'd be making
things even more chaotic.

00:09:04.502 --> 00:09:05.920 position:50% align:center
[HANAKO]
As soon as the problem's solved,

00:09:06.004 --> 00:09:07.339 position:50% align:center
then it's done.

00:09:07.422 --> 00:09:08.923 position:50% align:center
I can reappoint them.

00:09:09.007 --> 00:09:12.260 position:50% align:center
What do you say,
Mr. Tsuchigomori?

00:09:12.344 --> 00:09:13.553 position:50% align:center
Are you in?

00:09:13.636 --> 00:09:15.680 position:50% align:center
Absolutely not.

00:09:15.764 --> 00:09:16.890 position:50% align:center
Is what I'd like to say,

00:09:16.973 --> 00:09:19.809 position:50% align:center
but as you know,
I hate to stir conflict.

00:09:19.893 --> 00:09:22.479 position:50% align:center
If you demand my Yorishiro,
I'll comply.

00:09:22.562 --> 00:09:24.731 position:50% align:center
But that compliance
has one condition.

00:09:24.814 --> 00:09:26.191 position:50% align:center
What condition?

00:09:26.274 --> 00:09:27.692 position:50% align:center
[TSUCHIGOMORI] I want each
of you to tell me your

00:09:27.776 --> 00:09:29.569 position:50% align:center
juiciest secrets.

00:09:30.945 --> 00:09:33.823 position:50% align:center
--Say what?!
--Why our secrets?

00:09:33.907 --> 00:09:36.868 position:50% align:center
Why? Because I find it
entertaining, wouldn't you?

00:09:36.951 --> 00:09:39.829 position:50% align:center
And what if they refuse
to share that information?

00:09:39.913 --> 00:09:41.706 position:50% align:center
Should I prepare for battle?

00:09:41.790 --> 00:09:43.166 position:50% align:center
Oh, no.

00:09:43.249 --> 00:09:45.210 position:50% align:center
I'll hand you my Yorishiro,

00:09:45.293 --> 00:09:48.421 position:50% align:center
but my revenge will be
utilizing the PA system

00:09:48.505 --> 00:09:50.799 position:50% align:center
to tell the whole school
what I already know.

00:09:50.882 --> 00:09:52.050 position:50% align:center
[BOTH yell]

00:09:52.133 --> 00:09:55.470 position:50% align:center
So I'd give me something
to sink my teeth into.

00:09:55.553 --> 00:09:58.098 position:50% align:center
But I'll have fun either way.

00:09:58.181 --> 00:09:59.974 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:10:06.773 --> 00:10:09.234 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
Okay, I'll go first!

00:10:09.317 --> 00:10:11.569 position:50% align:center
My darkest secret is, uh,

00:10:11.653 --> 00:10:13.196 position:50% align:center
when I was in junior high,
I wrote love letters

00:10:13.279 --> 00:10:15.782 position:50% align:center
in a diary to an
imaginary boyfriend!

00:10:15.865 --> 00:10:16.783 position:50% align:center
I'll give it three.

00:10:16.866 --> 00:10:18.118 position:50% align:center
[NENE]
What? Why?

00:10:18.201 --> 00:10:20.704 position:50% align:center
For one, I knew you
were going to say that.

00:10:20.787 --> 00:10:23.748 position:50% align:center
